speak more to how

00:53:38.960 --> 00:53:41.330
physical health and
lifestyle behaviors impact

00:53:41.330 --> 00:53:43.550
mental health?"

00:53:43.550 --> 00:53:46.110
CATHERINE BIRNDORF:
So intertwined.

00:53:46.110 --> 00:53:48.860
I think that it's probably
false that we separate them.

00:53:48.860 --> 00:53:50.330
AMY SHAMUS: Oh, absolutely.

00:53:50.330 --> 00:53:52.330
And that's what "The
Clarity Cleanse" is about.

00:53:52.330 --> 00:53:53.620
So great question.

00:53:53.620 --> 00:53:56.780
I would certainly read it.

00:53:56.780 --> 00:53:59.029
CATHERINE BIRNDORF:
Yeah, I think--

00:53:59.029 --> 00:54:00.070
ELISE LOEHNEN: Vitamin B.

00:54:00.070 --> 00:54:01.611
CATHERINE BIRNDORF:
Vitamin B, right.

00:54:01.611 --> 00:54:06.140
I think you want to be
physically well so and not so

00:54:06.140 --> 00:54:06.680
stressed.

00:54:06.680 --> 00:54:09.350
You want to minimize
stress, maximize self-care,

00:54:09.350 --> 00:54:10.390
taking care of yourself.

00:54:10.390 --> 00:54:11.450
It's not selfish.

00:54:11.450 --> 00:54:14.300
It is self preserving,
self nourishing.

00:54:14.300 --> 00:54:16.730
Like the oxygen mask, you're
no good to anybody else

00:54:16.730 --> 00:54:18.260
if you're not OK.

00:54:18.260 --> 00:54:21.170
But you're no good to yourself
if you're not physically well

00:54:21.170 --> 00:54:25.820
enough, and I think that helps
you be as mentally well enough.

00:54:25.820 --> 00:54:27.320
Again, you don't
have to be perfect.

00:54:27.320 --> 00:54:29.120
Everything doesn't
have to be exact.

00:54:29.120 --> 00:54:33.785
But I think that they're
just so intertwined

00:54:33.785 --> 00:54:35.450
that you have to address both.

00:54:35.450 --> 00:54:38.180
And I think that becomes a
problem, because people--

00:54:38.180 --> 00:54:41.210
everyone knows to work
out, go to the gym.

00:54:41.210 --> 00:54:41.900
I'll be walking.

00:54:41.900 --> 00:54:44.650
Everyone else can be in the gym.

00:54:44.650 --> 00:54:47.450
But mental health has
to also be addressed.

00:54:47.450 --> 00:54:49.580
I said to someone the
other day, who said, wait,

00:54:49.580 --> 00:54:51.552
is therapy like
gym for your mind?

00:54:51.552 --> 00:54:53.260
It's like going to
the gym for your mind.

00:54:53.260 --> 00:54:53.520
Yeah.

00:54:53.520 --> 00:54:54.680
AMY SHAMUS: It's like
brushing your teeth.

00:54:54.680 --> 00:54:55.763
CATHERINE BIRNDORF: Right?

00:54:55.763 --> 00:54:58.460
So OK, not everyone's going
to go to therapy, though I

00:54:58.460 --> 00:55:00.237
kind of think they should.

00:55:00.237 --> 00:55:01.070
AMY SHAMUS: I agree.

00:55:01.070 --> 00:55:03.278
CATHERINE BIRNDORF: I think
almost anyone can use it,

00:55:03.278 --> 00:55:04.520
because we all have pasts.

00:55:04.520 --> 00:55:05.549
We all have baggage.

00:55:05.549 --> 00:55:08.090
We all have things to work out,
so that we don't revisit them

00:55:08.090 --> 00:55:11.000
on our children, as
we're talking about.

00:55:11.000 --> 00:55:15.470
And I think that you want to be
as well emotionally, mentally,

00:55:15.470 --> 00:55:16.160
as you can.

00:55:16.160 --> 00:55:17.900
And that will help
your physical health.

00:55:17.900 --> 00:55:19.760
They work in concert.

00:55:19.760 --> 00:55:23.390
And to ignore one, or to
only focus on the other

00:55:23.390 --> 00:55:24.440
is short sighted.

00:55:24.440 --> 00:55:25.550
AMY SHAMUS: Yeah.

00:55:25.550 --> 00:55:30.170
And again with Google, go
to MoMA and look up Concern.

00:55:30.170 --> 00:55:35.020
We have programs that we can
certainly get therapy sessions,

00:55:35.020 --> 00:55:36.020
